notesStmt.note: Translation of Euclid's Elements with geometrical figures, marginal and inserted notes.

respStmt.persName: Ṭūsī, Naṣīr al-Dīn Muḥammad ibn Muḥammad, 1201-1274
طوسي، نصير الدين محمد بن محمد,

supportDesc.extent: 175 foliated leaves : 205 x 140 (135 x 60) mm, bound to 205 x 135 mm

layoutDesc.layout: 19 long lines; wide margins for diagrams and marginalia.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black ink; marginal notations in nastaʻliq in black ink; pointed.

binding.p: Islamic binding. Light brown leather frame cover with darker brown leather sides, separate marbled paper pastedowns with stubs extending across the joints. Endbands with chevron-pattern secondary sewing.

origin.p: Likely copied in the mid- to late-19th century.

history.provenance: Given to D.E. Smith on April 8, 1933 in Iran. Note on inside cover "D.E. Smith No. 25 Commentary on Euclid. Gift from Dr. Sadiq.".
